Creating images with R

with a little bit of magick

Yvonne Liew

2023-03-07

My meme

My meme is a recreation of the classic Drake meme and it is about how I am a night owl. 

library(magick)

#note: this is a recreation of the Drake meme.

drake1 <- image_read('https://i.imgflip.com/t7px7.jpg') %>%
  image_scale("500X500!") %>%
  image_border("black", "10X10")

drake2 <- image_read('https://wompampsupport.azureedge.net/fetchimage?siteId=7575&v=2&jpgQuality=100&width=700&url=https%3A%2F%2Fi.kym-cdn.com%2Fentries%2Ficons%2Ffacebook%2F000%2F020%2F147%2Fdrake.jpg') %>%
  image_scale("500X500!") %>%
  image_border("black", "10X10")

early_text <- image_blank(width = 500, height = 500, color = '#FFFFFF') %>%
  image_annotate(text = "Sleeping early", 
                 color = "#000000", 
                 size = 75, 
                 font = "Arial", 
                 gravity = "center", 
                 boxcolor = "#FCF6DC") %>%
  image_border("black", "10X10")

late_text <- image_blank(width = 500, height = 500, color = '#FFFFFF') %>%
  image_annotate(text = "Sleeping late", 
                 color = "#000000", 
                 size = 80, 
                 font = "Arial", 
                 gravity = "center", 
                 boxcolor = "#FCF6DC") %>%
  image_border("black", "10X10")

first_row <- c(drake1, early_text) %>%
  image_append()

second_row <- c(drake2, late_text) %>%
  image_append()

# Line 26 stacks the first row and second row to create the full meme.
meme <- c(first_row, second_row) %>%
  image_append(stack = TRUE)

meme

meme %>% image_write("my_meme.png")

My animated GIF

My GIF is a countdown to New Years Day. It counts down from 3 to 1 and at the end it displays Happy New Year!. 

library(magick)

#Note: this gif is a countdown to new year's day.

background <- image_blank(width = 500, height = 500, color = '#FFFFFF') %>%
  image_scale("500X500!")

happy_background <- image_read("https://encrypted-tbn0.gstatic.com/images?q=tbn:ANd9GcRZtp56lutyYULW58NpPWbBVLwc-5R2HJFhQw&usqp=CAU") %>%
  image_scale("500X500!")

frame1 <- background %>%
  image_annotate(text = "3", size = 300, gravity = "center") %>%
  image_extent("500X500")

frame2 <- background %>%
  image_annotate(text = "2", size = 200, gravity = "center") %>%
  image_extent("500X500")

frame3 <- background %>%
  image_annotate(text = "1", size = 100, gravity = "center") %>%
  image_extent("500X500")

frame4 <- happy_background %>%
  image_annotate(text = "Happy New\nYear!", size = 80, gravity = "center", color = "white") %>%
  image_extent("500X500")

#Line 29 combines the 4 frames. There's a countdown, then it says "Happy New Year!"

frames <- c(frame1, frame2, frame3, frame4)

animation <- image_morph(frames) %>%
  image_animate(optimize = TRUE)

animation

animation %>% image_write("my_animation.gif")
